      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CERISE (2) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (19.90) at Angle Park behind Pure Gout in a TG1-4W. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Can go on with it. GRAPEFRUIT WILMA (1) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing fifth (31.62) at Angle Park last time. Must be included in calculations. ASTON GOSSET (5) stalked the lead from a middle box before hitting the front turning and lifting to score (17.18) at this track in a TG1-4W over 300m. The form out of his last race has been franked. Will go close again if runs up to latest.",
